      "id": 1,
      "text": "Plainedge was founded in 1687 when Thomas Powell bought land from the Marsapeque Indians as part of the Bethpage Purchase.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        2
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plainedge%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "Early settlers turned the area into cattle pasture before converting it into hay farms.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        3
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.longislandexchange.com/towns/plainedge/"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Cabbage and cucumber farms flourished until the early 1900s, when blight forced their abandonment.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        6
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.longislandexchange.com/towns/plainedge/"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "In 1690, a joint venture bought the West Neck area, expanding Plainedge’s western frontier.",
